cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.AI

This paper deals with word embeddings and their application to various types of data, including text data from U.S. Congressional speeches and the ArXiv, as well as grocery purchase data. Given this focus on language and data analysis, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). However, the paper also discusses hierarchical modeling and amortization, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and statistics, suggesting that it could also fit into categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper's focus on prediction and interpretation of data could place it in categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
